:[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/518"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–518","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/1327"},"text":"84 Stat. 1327","children":[],"tail":", § 805(2)(B); added "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"June 22, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/316/s11/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–316, § 11(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/233"},"text":"86 Stat. 233","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Apr. 7, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/272/s4007/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–272, § 4007(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/108"},"text":"100 Stat. 108","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"24315(g)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"45:644(2)(C).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Oct. 30, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/518/s805/2/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–518, § 805(2)(C)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/1340"},"text":"84 Stat. 1340","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"June 22, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/316/s11/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–316, § 11(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/233"},"text":"86 Stat. 233","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(2), the words “to . . . compensation” and “prescribed” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b)(1), before clause (A), the words “(beginning with 1973)” are omitted as executed. The word “complete” is substituted for “comprehensive and detailed” to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “under this chapter” are omitted as surplus. The word “revenues” is substituted for “receipts” for consistency. In clause (B), the words “may include recommendations for legislation” are substituted for “At the time of its annual report, the Corporation shall submit such legislative recommendations as it deems desirable”, the words “the method of computing the assistance” are substituted for “the manner and form in which the amount of such assistance should be computed”, and the words “of the assistance” are substituted for “from which such assistance should be derived”, to eliminate unnecessary words.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), the words “(beginning with 1974)” are omitted as executed. The word “prepare” is substituted for “transmit to the President and to the Congress by March 15 of each year” for clarity because the report is now part of the annual report under 49:308(a). The words “Beginning in 1976” are omitted as executed. The word “Secretary” is substituted for “Department of Transportation” because of 49:102(b). The words “submits under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s308/a"},"text":"section 308(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":"” are substituted for “to the Congress” for clarity."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d), the words “independent licensed public accountants certified or licensed by a regulatory authority of a State or other political subdivision of the United States” are omitted as obsolete because only certified public accountants are used for the audit. Only noncertified public accountants licensed before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-12-30"},"text":"December 30, 1970","children":[],"tail":", who were already conducting audits were allowed to continue. The words “or places” are omitted because of 1:1. The words “financial statements” are substituted for “accounts” because audits are performed on financial statements, not accounts. The words “independent” and “annual” are omitted as surplus. The text of 45:644(1)(B) (last sentence) is omitted as surplus because those requirements are included in “generally accepted auditing standards”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (e), the word “rules” is omitted as being synonymous with “regulations”. The words “or places” are omitted because of 1:1. The word “appropriate” is omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (f), the words “if required” are substituted for “To the extent . . . deems necessary” to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “the person conducting”, “The representatives of the Comptroller General”, “his representatives”, “as he may make of the financial transactions of the Corporation”, “things, or”, and “full” are omitted as surplus. The words “may keep” are substituted for “shall remain in possession and custody of” and “shall remain in the possession and custody of” to eliminate unnecessary words.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (g), the word “giving” is substituted for “The report to the Congress shall contain such” to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “as the Comptroller General may deem”, “as he may deem advisable”, “program, expenditure or other”, “observed in the course of the audit”, and “or made” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcb333a30-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idcb333a31-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990 and such Act, referred to in subsec. (b)(1)(D), (E), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/336"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–336","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-07-26"},"text":"July 26, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/327"},"text":"104 Stat. 327","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 126 (§ 12101 et seq.) of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s12101"},"text":"section 12101 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcb333a32-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2024—Subsec. (b)(1)(D), (E). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/205/s2/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–205, § 2(1)","children":[],"tail":", added subpars. (D) and (E)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(3), (4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/205/s2/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–205, § 2(2)","children":[],"tail":", added pars. (3) and (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Subsec. (a)(1)(I). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58/s22204/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58, § 22204(a)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (I)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(1)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58/s22206/c/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58, § 22206(c)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “the goal described in section 24902(a);” for “the goal of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s24902/b"},"text":"section 24902(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"; and”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(1)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58/s22206/c/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58, § 22206(c)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", (C), added subpar. (C)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/134"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–134","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (h)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idcb333a33-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idcb333a34-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Termination of Reporting Requirements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For termination, effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-05-15"},"text":"May 15, 2000","children":[],"tail":", of provisions in subsecs. (a), (b)(1), (c), and (d) of this section relating to requirements to submit regular periodic reports to Congress, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/66/s3003"},"text":"section 3003 of Pub. L. 104–66","children":[],"tail":", as amended, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s1113"},"text":"section 1113 of Title 31","children":[],"tail":", Money and Finance. See, also, the 3rd item on page 176 and the 6th and 7th items on page 204 of House Document No. 103–7."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idcb333a35-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Funding for Valuation of Amtrak’s Assets","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/447/dH/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–447, div. H, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/3221"},"text":"118 Stat. 3221","children":[],"tail":", provided in part: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/108/447/dH/tI"},"text":"“That the Secretary of Transportation is authorized to retain up to $4,000,000 of the funds provided to be used to retain a consultant or consultants to assist the Secretary in preparing a comprehensive valuation of Amtrak’s assets to be completed not later than ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 2005","children":[],"tail":": "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided further","children":[],"tail":", That these funds shall be available to the Secretary of Transportation until expended: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided further","children":[],"tail":", That this valuation shall to be used to retain a consultant or consultants to develop to the Secretary’s satisfaction a methodology for determining the avoidable and fully allocated costs of each Amtrak route: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided further","children":[],"tail":", That once the Secretary has approved the methodology for determining the avoidable and fully allocated costs of each Amtrak route, Amtrak shall apply that methodology in compiling an annual report to Congress on the avoidable and fully allocated costs of each of its routes, with the initial report for fiscal year 2005 to be submitted to the House and Senate Committees on Appropriations, the House Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure, and the Senate Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 2005","children":[],"tail":", and each subsequent report to be submitted within 90 days after the end of the fiscal year to which the report pertains.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idcb333a36-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Reports on Operating Losses","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/7/dI/tIII/s350"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–7, div. I, title III, § 350","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-02-20"},"text":"Feb. 20, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/419"},"text":"117 Stat. 419","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/108/7/dI/tIII/s350"},"text":"“On ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-02-15"},"text":"February 15, 2003","children":[],"tail":", and on each year thereafter, the National Railroad Passenger Corporation shall submit to the appropriate Congressional Committees a report detailing the per passenger operating loss on each rail line.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idcb333a37-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amtrak To Notify Congress of Lobbying Relationships","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/134/tIV/s414"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–134, title IV, § 414","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-12-02"},"text":"Dec. 2, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/2589"},"text":"111 Stat. 2589","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/105/134/tIV/s414"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"section","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":""},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"“If, at any time, during a fiscal year in which Amtrak receives Federal assistance, Amtrak enters into a consulting contract or similar arrangement, or a contract for lobbying, with a lobbying firm, an individual who is a lobbyist, or who is affiliated with a lobbying firm, as those terms are defined in section 3 of the Lobbying Disclosure Act of 1995 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s1602"},"text":"2 U.S.C. 1602","children":[],"tail":"), Amtrak shall notify the United States Senate Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation, and the United States House of Representatives Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure of—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the name of the individual or firm involved;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the purpose of the contract or arrangement; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"“(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the amount and nature of Amtrak’s financial obligation under the contract.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"This section applies only to contracts, renewals or extensions of contracts, or arrangements entered into after the date of the enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-12-02"},"text":"Dec. 2, 1997","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
